'''Generalized periodic epileptiform discharges''' ('''GPED'''s) are very rare abnormal patterns found in [[EEG]].<ref name="pmid12967574">{{cite journal |last1=Yemisci |first1=M |last2=Gurer |first2=G |last3=Saygi |first3=S |last4=Ciger |first4=A |title=Generalised periodic epileptiform discharges: clinical features, neuroradiological evaluation and prognosis in 37 adult patients. |journal=Seizure |date=October 2003 |volume=12 |issue=7 |pages=465-72 |pmid=12967574}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Andraus |first1=Maria Emilia Cosenza |last2=Andraus |first2=Cesar Fantezia |last3=Alves-Leon |first3=Soniza Vieira |title=Periodic EEG patterns: importance of their recognition and clinical significance |journal=Arquivos de Neuro-Psiquiatria |date=February 2012 |volume=70 |issue=2 |pages=145–151 |doi=10.1590/S0004-282X2012000200014 |url=http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0004-282X2012000200014}}</ref>

==Types==
Based on the interval between the discharges they are classified as:<ref name="pmid12967574" />
* [[Periodic short-interval diffuse discharges]] (PSIDDs)
* [[Periodic long-interval diffuse discharges]] (PLIDDs)
* [[Burst suppression]] patterns

